records.title: Analysis of Algorithms
records.subject: CSE
records.description: Presents time and space complexity of computer algorithms. Includes algorithm classes, such as divide-and-conquer, greedy, dynamic programming and backtracking; techniques for solving recurrence equations; graph algorithms; searching and sorting; and deterministic and nondeterministic polynomial time problem classes. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010 and MTH 1002.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Presents time and space complexity of computer algorithms. Includes algorithm classes, such as divide-and-conquer, greedy, dynamic programming and backtracking; techniques for solving recurrence equations; graph algorithms; searching and sorting; and deterministic and nondeterministic polynomial time problem classes. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010 and MTH 1002.)

records.title: Network Programming
records.subject: CSE
records.description: Covers design and implementation of programs that communicate with other programs across a computer network. Includes common protocols, network management and debugging tools, server- and client-side networking, presentation layer, secure socket layer, multithreading, exceptions, remote procedure call and peer-to-peer networking. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers design and implementation of programs that communicate with other programs across a computer network. Includes common protocols, network management and debugging tools, server- and client-side networking, presentation layer, secure socket layer, multithreading, exceptions, remote procedure call and peer-to-peer networking. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010.)

records.title: Compiler Theory and Design
records.subject: CSE
records.description: Covers extensively the major topics of compiler design. Includes lexical analysis, scanner-generator tools, parsing, syntax-directed translation, static semantic checking, storage organizations, code generation and code optimization. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010 and CSE 3120.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers extensively the major topics of compiler design. Includes lexical analysis, scanner-generator tools, parsing, syntax-directed translation, static semantic checking, storage organizations, code generation and code optimization. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010 and CSE 3120.)

records.title: Computer Graphics
records.subject: CSE
records.description: Presents the graphics pipeline for polygonal-based models. Includes mathematical concepts and data structures for graphics, coordinate systems, clipping, scan conversion, hidden-object detection, rendering, color models and graphics programming standards. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2050 and MTH 1002.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Presents the graphics pipeline for polygonal-based models. Includes mathematical concepts and data structures for graphics, coordinate systems, clipping, scan conversion, hidden-object detection, rendering, color models and graphics programming standards. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2050 and MTH 1002.)

records.title: Artificial Intelligence
records.subject: CSE
records.description: Introduces the theoretical foundations of artificial intelligence, focusing on the areas of automated reasoning, search and heuristics. Introduces an AI language to implement concepts. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces the theoretical foundations of artificial intelligence, focusing on the areas of automated reasoning, search and heuristics. Introduces an AI language to implement concepts. (Recommended: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 2010.)

records.description: Covers the mathematical and programming skills needed by data scientists. Focuses on mathematical concepts and their real-world application to data science. records.title: Computer Applications Lab
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Offers a broad background in computer applications, strongly emphasizing computer-aided design. Briefly discusses word processing, spreadsheet coding and PowerPoint(r) presentations. (CL)
records.description_with_prereqs: Offers a broad background in computer applications, strongly emphasizing computer-aided design. Briefly discusses word processing, spreadsheet coding and PowerPoint(r) presentations. (CL)

records.title: Construction Measurements
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers measurement of distances, elevations and angles; statistical errors and data adjustment; working with coordinates; topographic mapping and photogrammetry; global positioning systems (GPS); geographic information systems (GIS); and computer applications.
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers measurement of distances, elevations and angles; statistical errors and data adjustment; working with coordinates; topographic mapping and photogrammetry; global positioning systems (GPS); geographic information systems (GIS); and computer applications. (Prerequisites: CVE 1001, CVE 1001)

records.description: Covers measurement of distances, elevations and angles; statistical errors and data adjustment; working with coordinates; topographic mapping and photogrammetry; global positioning systems (GPS); geographic information systems (GIS); and computer applications.

records.description: Covers measurement of distances, elevations and angles; statistical errors and data adjustment; working with coordinates; topographic mapping and photogrammetry; global positioning systems (GPS); geographic information systems (GIS); and computer applications.

records.title: Soils and Foundations
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Studies the application of mechanics and hydraulics to the analysis of soils. Includes engineering geology, index properties, classification, compaction, effective stress, permeability, consolidation, and shear strength behavior of soil, as well as application to the design of foundations and retaining walls.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the application of mechanics and hydraulics to the analysis of soils. Includes engineering geology, index properties, classification, compaction, effective stress, permeability, consolidation, and shear strength behavior of soil, as well as application to the design of foundations and retaining walls. (Prerequisites: MAE 3083)

records.title: Soil Mechanics Lab
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics.
records.description_with_prereqs: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics. (Prerequisites: CVE 3020, CVE 3020)

records.title: Soil Mechanics Lab
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics.
records.description_with_prereqs: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics. (Prerequisites: CVE 3020, CVE 3020)

records.title: Soil Mechanics Lab
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics.
records.description_with_prereqs: Offers experiments in the sampling and testing of soil as an engineering material, to support topics in soil mechanics. (Prerequisites: CVE 3020, CVE 3020)

records.title: Water and Wastewater Sys
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers the topics necessary to design potable water and domestic wastewater utility systems for land development projects. Includes the treatment and distribution of potable water and the collection and treatment of wastewater.
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers the topics necessary to design potable water and domestic wastewater utility systems for land development projects. Includes the treatment and distribution of potable water and the collection and treatment of wastewater. (Prerequisites: CHM 1101, CVE 1001, CVE 3030, CVE 3030)

records.title: Engr Econ and Planning
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Presents economic evaluation of engineering alternatives. Includes time value of money, replacement alternatives, benefit/cost analysis, minimum cost analysis, depreciation, taxes and inflation. (Requirement: Junior standing.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Presents economic evaluation of engineering alternatives. Includes time value of money, replacement alternatives, benefit/cost analysis, minimum cost analysis, depreciation, taxes and inflation. (Requirement: Junior standing.)

records.title: Steel Structures
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Studies the design of various elements of steel structures including tension members, beams, columns, beam-columns and connections. Introduces the AISC codes. Includes a design project.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the design of various elements of steel structures including tension members, beams, columns, beam-columns and connections. Introduces the AISC codes. Includes a design project. (Prerequisites: CVE 3015)

records.title: Timber Structures
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers the engineering properties of timber and their effect on design of timber structures. Studies the design of various elements of timber structures including tension members, beams, bean-columns, diaphragms and connections according to the NDS ASD specification. Includes a design project.
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers the engineering properties of timber and their effect on design of timber structures. Studies the design of various elements of timber structures including tension members, beams, bean-columns, diaphragms and connections according to the NDS ASD specification. Includes a design project. (Prerequisites: CVE 3015)

records.title: Hydraulics and Hydrology
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Includes steady flow in open channels, analysis of water surface profiles, channel design; measurements and estimation of components in the hydrologic cycle; unit hydrograph theory; statistical design methods; and hydrologic routing.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes steady flow in open channels, analysis of water surface profiles, channel design; measurements and estimation of components in the hydrologic cycle; unit hydrograph theory; statistical design methods; and hydrologic routing. (Prerequisites: CVE 3030)

records.title: Urban Hydrology
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Uses state-of-the-art water-quality and water-quantity computer models to predict the impact of urbanization on receiving waters. Students design a stormwater management system as a project.
records.description_with_prereqs: Uses state-of-the-art water-quality and water-quantity computer models to predict the impact of urbanization on receiving waters. Students design a stormwater management system as a project. (Prerequisites: CVE 4032)

records.title: Leading Construction Ops
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers specialized application of leadership fundamentals and team building to construction operations. Focuses on the basic principles of leadership including motivation, organizational dynamics, team formation and conflict resolution. Examines construction operations, work practices and ethics in the business environment. (Requirement: Junior standing.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers specialized application of leadership fundamentals and team building to construction operations. Focuses on the basic principles of leadership including motivation, organizational dynamics, team formation and conflict resolution. Examines construction operations, work practices and ethics in the business environment. (Requirement: Junior standing.)

records.title: Design Project 1
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Develops a real world, peer reviewed, team design project. Students review alternatives and present a schedule and cost estimate. Professional and ethical issues are discussed. Project is completed in CVE 4092. Oral and written reports and a final team presentation are required. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Develops a real world, peer reviewed, team design project. Students review alternatives and present a schedule and cost estimate. Professional and ethical issues are discussed. Project is completed in CVE 4092. Oral and written reports and a final team presentation are required. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Q)

records.title: Design Project 2
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Proposal developed in CVE 4091 is completed. Oral and written reports and a final team oral presentation and report required. Also includes discussion of professional and ethical issues. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Q)

records.title: Independent Study
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Independent study undertaken on a cooperative basis between a student and a member of the faculty. Typically, it is a short-term research-related project. May be repeated for a maximum of six credits. (Requirement: Department head approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Independent study undertaken on a cooperative basis between a student and a member of the faculty. Typically, it is a short-term research-related project. May be repeated for a maximum of six credits. (Requirement: Department head approval.)

records.title: Adv Reinforced Concrete
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers advanced topics in the analysis and design of reinforced concrete structures. Includes two-way slabs, torsions, strut-and-tie method, and slender and biaxial columns. Introduces the basic concepts of prestressed concrete. Requires students to complete a design project. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CVE 4016 Reinforced Concrete Structures.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers advanced topics in the analysis and design of reinforced concrete structures. Includes two-way slabs, torsions, strut-and-tie method, and slender and biaxial columns. Introduces the basic concepts of prestressed concrete. Requires students to complete a design project. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CVE 4016 Reinforced Concrete Structures.)

records.title: Des Con in Urban Hydrology
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Uses state-of-the-art water-quality and water-quantity computer models to predict the impact of urbanization on receiving waters. Students design a stormwater management system as a project.
records.description_with_prereqs: Uses state-of-the-art water-quality and water-quantity computer models to predict the impact of urbanization on receiving waters. Students design a stormwater management system as a project. (Prerequisites: CVE 4032)

records.title: Pavement Design
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers stresses, strain and deflections in both flexible and rigid pavements; flexible and rigid pavement materials testing techniques; pavement designs for roads and airports; nondestructive pavement evaluation; and pavement management systems. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CVE 3020.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers stresses, strain and deflections in both flexible and rigid pavements; flexible and rigid pavement materials testing techniques; pavement designs for roads and airports; nondestructive pavement evaluation; and pavement management systems. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CVE 3020.)

records.title: Transportation Planning
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Covers demand analysis for transportation planning. Includes fundamental modeling techniques (trip generation, trip distribution, mode choice (modal split), traffic assignment), surveys and data requirements. Also includes evaluation of transportation alternatives and policy implications. Uses GIS transportation software. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 4060 and MTH 5401.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers demand analysis for transportation planning. Includes fundamental modeling techniques (trip generation, trip distribution, mode choice (modal split), traffic assignment), surveys and data requirements. Also includes evaluation of transportation alternatives and policy implications. Uses GIS transportation software. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 4060 and MTH 5401.)

records.title: Leading Construction Operation
records.subject: CVE
records.description: Fundamentals of leadership and team building to construction operations. Focuses on the basic principles of leadership including team formation, motivation, organizational dynamics and conflict resolution. Examines construction operations and characteristics, ethics in the business environment and its relationship to sound leadership principles.
records.description_with_prereqs: Fundamentals of leadership and team building to construction operations. Focuses on the basic principles of leadership including team formation, motivation, organizational dynamics and conflict resolution. Examines construction operations and characteristics, ethics in the business environment and its relationship to sound leadership principles.

records.title: Cooperative Education 1
records.subject: CWE
records.description: Prepares students for professional careers by integrating alternate periods of academic study and career-related work experience. Places students in private industry, business and public agencies. Requires specific academic standards and recommendation by the university to be eligible. Registration for three credits classifies student as full time, and credits may be applied as free elective credit in most programs. Also requires co-op coordinator approval of appropriate course prior to registration. Grades are pass/fail (P/F) only. (Requirement: Completion of 24 credit hours with at least a 2.5 GPA.)

records.title: Comp and Info Security
records.subject: CYB
records.description: Examines concepts of modern computer security from a practical point of view. Includes vulnerability analysis, threat modeling and risk assessment, and techniques for asset protection. Discusses economic, legal and ethical issues in computer security. Emphasizes a systemwide view of security and includes a survey of current literature.
records.description_with_prereqs: Examines concepts of modern computer security from a practical point of view. Includes vulnerability analysis, threat modeling and risk assessment, and techniques for asset protection. Discusses economic, legal and ethical issues in computer security. Emphasizes a systemwide view of security and includes a survey of current literature.

records.title: Secure Operating Systems
records.subject: CYB
records.description: Studies security within operating systems. Provides understanding of the design challenges, software mechanisms and issues affecting operating system security. Includes the ability to compare the security merits of different operating systems. Uses case studies.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies security within operating systems. Provides understanding of the design challenges, software mechanisms and issues affecting operating system security. Includes the ability to compare the security merits of different operating systems. Uses case studies. (Prerequisites: CYB 5272)

records.title: Secure Data Coms & Networks
records.subject: CYB
records.description: Explores data communications, networking and network security. Provides a foundation of networking including TCP/IP, other communications protocols and routing. Uses practical network security schemes to enable students to identify and implement a variety of network and communications security measures. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 5231 or ECE 5534, or instructor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Explores data communications, networking and network security. Provides a foundation of networking including TCP/IP, other communications protocols and routing. Uses practical network security schemes to enable students to identify and implement a variety of network and communications security measures. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to CSE 5231 or ECE 5534, or instructor approval.) (Prerequisites: CYB 5272)

records.title: Principles of Accounting 1
records.subject: EAC
records.description: Introduces the financial environment, financial statements, the accounting cycle and the theoretical framework of accounting measurement, emphasizing mechanics, measurement theory and the economic environment. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces the financial environment, financial statements, the accounting cycle and the theoretical framework of accounting measurement, emphasizing mechanics, measurement theory and the economic environment. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.)

records.title: Intermediate Accounting 1
records.subject: EAC
records.description: Studies the development of generally accepted accounting principles and valuation models in their application to financial statement presentations. Includes in-depth coverage of the preparation and use of accounting information based on current accounting standards of financial accounting. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the development of generally accepted accounting principles and valuation models in their application to financial statement presentations. Includes in-depth coverage of the preparation and use of accounting information based on current accounting standards of financial accounting. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.) (Prerequisites: EAC 2212)

records.title: Intermediate Accounting 2
records.subject: EAC
records.description: Continues EAC 3211. Includes the valuation of liabilities and equities, revenue realization, accounting changes, income taxes, leases and financial statement disclosures. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Continues EAC 3211. Includes the valuation of liabilities and equities, revenue realization, accounting changes, income taxes, leases and financial statement disclosures. (Requirement: Must be enrolled in Florida Tech Online.) (Prerequisites: EAC 3211)

records.title: Digital Logic
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Studies the design of specialized processors. Introduces generalized processors. Includes state diagram, state assignment, transition diagram, combinatorial and sequential logic, programmable logic devices, dynamic registers, counters and memories. Provides extensive hands-on experience including logic simulation, hardware implementation, Web experience, circuit drawing and diagramming software.

records.title: Circuit Theory 1
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Includes concepts of transient and steady-state behavior of passive electrical circuits; techniques for circuit analysis including mesh and nodal analysis and equivalent circuits; first- and second-order circuits, superposition, Laplace transform techniques; and lab projects.

records.title: Circuit Theory 2
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Continues ECE 2111. Includes phasors and steady-state response; AC power and two-port equivalent circuits and transfer functions; Fourier analysis transforms analysis, Laplace transforms; and lab projects.

records.title: Soft/Hardware Integration
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Progresses from developing software/hardware modules to the vertical system of application use interfaces. Applies current software engineering techniques including data structures to integrate software and hardware using modern programming languages (e.g., C++). (CL)
records.description_with_prereqs: Progresses from developing software/hardware modules to the vertical system of application use interfaces. records.title: Junior Design
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Introduces the concepts, principles and methodology of collaborative electrical or computer engineering design through seminars, discussions and interaction with seniors completing their capstone design projects. Students form teams and study the feasibility of potential senior project selections. (Requirement: Junior standing.) (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces the concepts, principles and methodology of collaborative electrical or computer engineering design through seminars, discussions and interaction with seniors completing their capstone design projects. Students form teams and study the feasibility of potential senior project selections. (Requirement: Junior standing.) (Q) (Prerequisites: CHM 1101, CHM 1101)

records.title: Electron Devices
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Studies semiconductor materials and physics, electrons and holes, semiconductor diodes, bipolar transistors and field effect devices.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies semiconductor materials and physics, electrons and holes, semiconductor diodes, bipolar transistors and field effect devices. (Prerequisites: MTH 2201, PHY 2003)

records.title: Electromagnetic Waves
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Addresses validity of circuit principles at high frequencies, electromagnetic wave on lines, impedance measurements using Smith chart, impedance matching techniques, waveguides and fiber-optical transmission systems, antennas and radiation waves, satellite data links and radar systems.
records.description_with_prereqs: Addresses validity of circuit principles at high frequencies, electromagnetic wave on lines, impedance measurements using Smith chart, impedance matching techniques, waveguides and fiber-optical transmission systems, antennas and radiation waves, satellite data links and radar systems. (Prerequisites: MTH 2001, PHY 2002)

records.title: Microcomputer Systems 2
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Introduces advanced concepts of software development for Embedded DSP hardware. Covers data coding and transmission, and video image processing. Requires project research and development.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces advanced concepts of software development for Embedded DSP hardware. Covers data coding and transmission, and video image processing. Requires project research and development. (Prerequisites: ECE 3551)

records.title: Digital Electronics
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Covers the fundamentals of digital electronics. Emphasizes analytical reasoning and integrated circuits. Discusses logic families and large-scale circuits. Uses electronic design automation tools such as VHDL and Quartus 11.
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers the fundamentals of digital electronics. Emphasizes analytical reasoning and integrated circuits. Discusses logic families and large-scale circuits. Uses electronic design automation tools such as VHDL and Quartus 11. (Prerequisites: ECE 2111)

records.title: Electronics Design
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Includes analysis and design of analog microelectronic circuits. Includes differential and multistage amplifiers, frequency response, feedback, output stages, analog integrated circuits, fibers and waveform-shaping circuits.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes analysis and design of analog microelectronic circuits. Includes differential and multistage amplifiers, frequency response, feedback, output stages, analog integrated circuits, fibers and waveform-shaping circuits. (Prerequisites: ECE 3111)

records.title: Electronics Design
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Includes analysis and design of analog microelectronic circuits. Includes differential and multistage amplifiers, frequency response, feedback, output stages, analog integrated circuits, fibers and waveform-shaping circuits.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes analysis and design of analog microelectronic circuits. Includes differential and multistage amplifiers, frequency response, feedback, output stages, analog integrated circuits, fibers and waveform-shaping circuits. (Prerequisites: ECE 3111)

records.title: Communication Systems
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Includes review of signals in electrical communication; Fourier transform, noise and signal-to-noise ratio, power spectral density and autocorrelation function, linear (amplitude) modulation; exponential (angle) modulation; generation and detection of amplitude and angle modulated waves; sampling theory.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes review of signals in electrical communication; Fourier transform, noise and signal-to-noise ratio, power spectral density and autocorrelation function, linear (amplitude) modulation; exponential (angle) modulation; generation and detection of amplitude and angle modulated waves; sampling theory. (Prerequisites: ECE 3222)

records.title: System Design 2
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Applies engineering design fundamentals to student design projects. Includes the study of the design process and related topics such as optimization techniques, reliability prediction, engineering economics, safety, aesthetics, ethics and social impact. Students carry out a project from conception through design, fabrication, testing and delivery. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Applies engineering design fundamentals to student design projects. Includes the study of the design process and related topics such as optimization techniques, reliability prediction, engineering economics, safety, aesthetics, ethics and social impact. Students carry out a project from conception through design, fabrication, testing and delivery. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Q) (Prerequisites: ECE 4241)

records.title: Spc Top in Elec/Comp Engr
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Offers topics in selected fields of computer and electrical engineering.
records.description_with_prereqs: Offers topics in selected fields of computer and electrical engineering.

records.title: Electrooptic Dev & Sys
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Discusses the theory of operation of key photonic/fiber-optic devices used in a wide variety of electronic systems. Devices include lasers, light emitting diodes, photodetectors, CCD arrays, liquid crystal displays, optical fibers, etc. Explains the basic operation of various electrooptic systems.
records.description_with_prereqs: Discusses the theory of operation of key photonic/fiber-optic devices used in a wide variety of electronic systems. Devices include lasers, light emitting diodes, photodetectors, CCD arrays, liquid crystal displays, optical fibers, etc. Explains the basic operation of various electrooptic systems. (Prerequisites: ECE 3442, ECE 3442, PHY 2003)

records.title: Virtual Instrument Lab
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Lectures and experiments in programming, data acquisition and analysis of virtual instruments using state-of-the-art and industry standard virtual instrumentation software and hardware tools. (Requirement: Senior standing in ECE or instructor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Lectures and experiments in programming, data acquisition and analysis of virtual instruments using state-of-the-art and industry standard virtual instrumentation software and hardware tools. (Requirement: Senior standing in ECE or instructor approval.)

records.title: Computer Communications
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Theory, design and analysis of computer communication systems. Includes TCP/IP, Internet, the World Wide Web, ISO-OSI network architecture, LANs, wireless communications, satellite networks, UNIX network programming, network modeling and simulation.
records.description_with_prereqs: Theory, design and analysis of computer communication systems. Includes TCP/IP, Internet, the World Wide Web, ISO-OSI network architecture, LANs, wireless communications, satellite networks, UNIX network programming, network modeling and simulation. (Prerequisites: ECE 2551)

records.title: Elec & Electronic Circuits
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Studies circuit theory for nonelectrical engineering students; transient and steady-state behavior of passive linear-lumped-parameter electric circuits; and AC circuit theory, network equations, network theorems; transfer functions and equivalent circuits. Noncredit for electrical and computer engineering majors except as Free Elective.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies circuit theory for nonelectrical engineering students; transient and steady-state behavior of passive linear-lumped-parameter electric circuits; and AC circuit theory, network equations, network theorems; transfer functions and equivalent circuits. Noncredit for electrical and computer engineering majors except as Free Elective. (Prerequisites: MTH 2001, PHY 2002)

records.title: Elec & Electronic Circuits
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Studies circuit theory for nonelectrical engineering students; transient and steady-state behavior of passive linear-lumped-parameter electric circuits; and AC circuit theory, network equations, network theorems; transfer functions and equivalent circuits. Noncredit for electrical and computer engineering majors except as Free Elective.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies circuit theory for nonelectrical engineering students; transient and steady-state behavior of passive linear-lumped-parameter electric circuits; and AC circuit theory, network equations, network theorems; transfer functions and equivalent circuits. Noncredit for electrical and computer engineering majors except as Free Elective. (Prerequisites: MTH 2001, PHY 2002)

records.title: Multimedia Communications
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Introduces multimedia, continuous and discrete media, multimedia data compression, image coding and video coding basics, JPEG and MPEG standards, multimedia networking, multimedia over Internet, multimedia over wireless networks.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces multimedia, continuous and discrete media, multimedia data compression, image coding and video coding basics, JPEG and MPEG standards, multimedia networking, multimedia over Internet, multimedia over wireless networks.

records.title: Linear Systems 1
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Studies linear spaces, linear operators and matrix calculus; mathematical description of linear dynamic systems, the relation between state variable descriptions and system transfer functions; controllability and observability of systems, realization of rational transfer function matrices and introduces nonlinear analysis.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies linear spaces, linear operators and matrix calculus; mathematical description of linear dynamic systems, the relation between state variable descriptions and system transfer functions; controllability and observability of systems, realization of rational transfer function matrices and introduces nonlinear analysis.

records.title: Satellite Communications
records.subject: ECE
records.description: A comprehensive study of the systems aspects of satellite communications, with emphasis on digital communications. Includes an analysis of AWGN channels, performance degradation caused by band limiting, nonlinearities, phase noise, etc. Presents a survey of existing operational satellite systems.
records.description_with_prereqs: A comprehensive study of the systems aspects of satellite communications, with emphasis on digital communications. Includes an analysis of AWGN channels, performance degradation caused by band limiting, nonlinearities, phase noise, etc. Presents a survey of existing operational satellite systems.

records.title: Radar Systems
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Covers characteristics of radar, prediction of range and performance, types of radar (pulse-Doppler, MTI, CW, etc.); modern radar technologies, phased-array systems, clutter, jamming; and introduces signal processing methods.
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers characteristics of radar, prediction of range and performance, types of radar (pulse-Doppler, MTI, CW, etc.); modern radar technologies, phased-array systems, clutter, jamming; and introduces signal processing methods.

records.title: Theory of Neural Networks
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Includes learning in a single neuron, single- and multi-layer perceptrons, recurrent neural networks, structured neural networks, neural networks to perform principal component analysis, principal component regression and partial least squares regression.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes learning in a single neuron, single- and multi-layer perceptrons, recurrent neural networks, structured neural networks, neural networks to perform principal component analysis, principal component regression and partial least squares regression.

records.title: Spc Top in Photonics
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Topics of current interest in the technical literature on photonics.
records.description_with_prereqs: Topics of current interest in the technical literature on photonics.

records.title: Antennas 2
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Equivalence principles; vector diffraction and its application to horn and reflector antennas; antenna pattern synthesis.
records.description_with_prereqs: Equivalence principles; vector diffraction and its application to horn and reflector antennas; antenna pattern synthesis.

records.title: Speech Recognition
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Basic approaches in speech recognition, dynamic time warping, hidden Markov models and neural networks.
records.description_with_prereqs: Basic approaches in speech recognition, dynamic time warping, hidden Markov models and neural networks.

records.title: Computer Systems
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Presents advanced treatment of the enduring concepts underlying all computer (hardware/software) systems. Covers the fundamental concepts in hardware/software required to create systems that operate correctly across a wide range of operating conditions and run-time parameters. Emphasizes performance analysis. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to ECE 4551.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Presents advanced treatment of the enduring concepts underlying all computer (hardware/software) systems. Covers the fundamental concepts in hardware/software required to create systems that operate correctly across a wide range of operating conditions and run-time parameters. Emphasizes performance analysis. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to ECE 4551.)

records.title: Embedded/Real-Time Sys
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Introduces embedded and real-time systems including resource-constrained systems, real-time scheduling including multiprocessor scheduling, real-time operating systems (kernels), real-time communication, real-time programming languages, performance analysis, reliability and fault-tolerance, and real-time system requirements and design methods.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces embedded and real-time systems including resource-constrained systems, real-time scheduling including multiprocessor scheduling, real-time operating systems (kernels), real-time communication, real-time programming languages, performance analysis, reliability and fault-tolerance, and real-time system requirements and design methods.

records.title: Android Embedded Appl Dev
records.subject: ECE
records.description: Introduces the fundamental principles of the architecture and programming of Android-based systems. Discusses current technology and development practices for applications in the Android operating system. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to ECE 3551.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces the fundamental principles of the architecture and programming of Android-based systems. Discusses current technology and development practices for applications in the Android operating system. (Requirement: Background knowledge equivalent to ECE 3551.)

records.description: Provides an opportunity to gain practical experience in industries related to electrical or computer engineering. Students are placed in an industrial environment under the supervision of a practicing engineer. (Requirement: Graduate standing.)

records.title: Survey of Sci 2: Life Sci
records.subject: EDS
records.description: Facilitates student understanding of laws, phenomena and processes of cellular and human biology, and to address selected current topics in ecology and environmental science.
records.description_with_prereqs: Facilitates student understanding of laws, phenomena and processes of cellular and human biology, and to address selected current topics in ecology and environmental science.

records.subject: EDS
records.description: Facilitates student understanding of laws, phenomena and processes of cellular and human biology, and to address selected current topics in ecology and environmental science.

records.title: Approaches to Teaching
records.subject: EDS
records.description: Acts as the first step in exploring teaching in science or mathematics. Provides early field experience in teaching. Introduces the theory and practice necessary to design and deliver instruction. Requires student to teach at the elementary level in local public school and student teams to present lessons to grades three to five.
records.description_with_prereqs: Acts as the first step in exploring teaching in science or mathematics. Provides early field experience in teaching. Introduces the theory and practice necessary to design and deliver instruction. Requires student to teach at the elementary level in local public school and student teams to present lessons to grades three to five.

records.title: Inquiry-Based Lesson Des
records.subject: EDS
records.description: Acts as second step in exploring teaching in science or mathematics. Covers the middle school environment. Includes inquiry-based lesson analysis, design and assessment. Requires students to be assigned according to interest to a middle school mentor teacher. Includes observation and teaching three quest inquiry-based lessons as part of student team.
records.description_with_prereqs: Acts as second step in exploring teaching in science or mathematics. Covers the middle school environment. Includes inquiry-based lesson analysis, design and assessment. Requires students to be assigned according to interest to a middle school mentor teacher. Includes observation and teaching three quest inquiry-based lessons as part of student team. (Prerequisites: EDS 1502)

records.title: Classroom Interaction
records.subject: EDS
records.description: Provides an overview of principles for teaching middle and secondary school mathematics or science. Explores the roles of content, pedagogy, curriculum and technology. records.title: Research Methods

Includes how scientists develop new knowledge and insights such as those eventually used in textbooks and taught in conventional classes. (Q) (Requirement: Instructor approval or prerequisite course.)

records.title: Protrack Coop Ed Prep
records.subject: EPE
records.description: Prepares Protrack students for cooperative education experiences and develops career planning and job search skills and techniques. Teaches the fundamentals of career exploration, resume development, interviewing skills and special job search techniques. Also covers workplace etiquette and ethics to help make a smooth transition to the workplace. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Prepares Protrack students for cooperative education experiences and develops career planning and job search skills and techniques. Teaches the fundamentals of career exploration, resume development, interviewing skills and special job search techniques. Also covers workplace etiquette and ethics to help make a smooth transition to the workplace. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA.)

records.title: Protrack Coop Ed
records.subject: EPE
records.description: Prepares students for professional careers by integrating alternate periods of academic study and career-related work experience. Includes work in private industry, business and public agencies. Classifies student as full time when registered for three credits. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Prepares students for professional careers by integrating alternate periods of academic study and career-related work experience. Includes work in private industry, business and public agencies. Classifies student as full time when registered for three credits. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.) (Prerequisites: EPE 1000)

records.title: Protrack Coop Ed
records.subject: EPE
records.description: Prepares students for professional careers by integrating alternate periods of academic study and career-related work experience. Includes work in private industry, business and public agencies. Classifies student as full time when registered for three credits. Can be applied as free elective credit. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Prepares students for professional careers by integrating alternate periods of academic study and career-related work experience. Includes work in private industry, business and public agencies. Classifies student as full time when registered for three credits. Can be applied as free elective credit. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.) (Prerequisites: EPE 1100)

records.title: Engr Protrack Coop Ed
records.subject: EPE
records.description: Prepares students for professional careers. Students work on engineering projects including one or more of the following realistic constraints: economic, environmental, social, political, ethical, health, safety, security and manufacturing. Classifies student as full time. Can be used for a maximum of three credits of technical elective. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Prepares students for professional careers. Students work on engineering projects including one or more of the following realistic constraints: economic, environmental, social, political, ethical, health, safety, security and manufacturing. Classifies student as full time. Can be used for a maximum of three credits of technical elective. (Requirements: Enrollment in Protrack program, 3.0 cumulative GPA and coop coordinator approval.) (Prerequisites: EPE 2100)

records.title: Strategies for Success
records.subject: FYE
records.description: Helps academically at-risk students during the first two years of their degree program identify and adopt effective strategies to improve study skills, time management and academic performance.

records.title: Creative/Design Thinking
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Introduces creativity and design thinking. Includes how to state and solve messy problems using out-of-the-box approaches; how to design in a team and recruit those who will be potential recipients of the product; story-telling and story boarding; cartoon generation; and parallel thinking.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces creativity and design thinking. Includes how to state and solve messy problems using out-of-the-box approaches; how to design in a team and recruit those who will be potential recipients of the product; story-telling and story boarding; cartoon generation; and parallel thinking.

records.title: Tangible Interactive Sys
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Introduces cognitive and physical function analysis, cyber-physical systems, tangibility, virtual engineering, flexibility, sustainability, human-centered design, maturity, complexity and human systems integration.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces cognitive and physical function analysis, cyber-physical systems, tangibility, virtual engineering, flexibility, sustainability, human-centered design, maturity, complexity and human systems integration.

records.title: Thesis
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Research and preparation of a thesis under the direction of a member of the graduate faculty. A maximum of six credit hours may be applied toward the master of science degree requirements. (Requirement: Thesis supervisor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Research and preparation of a thesis under the direction of a member of the graduate faculty. A maximum of six credit hours may be applied toward the master of science degree requirements. (Requirement: Thesis supervisor approval.)

records.title: Life-Critical Systems
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Requires students to develop and evaluate a synthesis of life-critical systems (LCS) illustrated by space systems, aeronautics, nuclear energy systems and various emergency systems. Improves knowledge and skills of the differences between technology-centered and human-centered design of LCS.
records.description_with_prereqs: Requires students to develop and evaluate a synthesis of life-critical systems (LCS) illustrated by space systems, aeronautics, nuclear energy systems and various emergency systems. Improves knowledge and skills of the differences between technology-centered and human-centered design of LCS.

records.title: Cognitive Engineering
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Discusses cognitive engineering and human-centered design of life-critical systems. Covers human-centered automation, human reliability and safety, risk-taking and management, cognitive modeling and cognitive function analysis, situation awareness, decision-making, use cases, scenario-based design and product integration.
records.description_with_prereqs: Discusses cognitive engineering and human-centered design of life-critical systems. Covers human-centered automation, human reliability and safety, risk-taking and management, cognitive modeling and cognitive function analysis, situation awareness, decision-making, use cases, scenario-based design and product integration.

records.title: Complexity Analysis
records.subject: HCD
records.description: Discusses complexity analysis from various points of view to the benefit of human-centered design. Covers how large numbers of relatively simple entities organize themselves without any central controller acting collectively to create patterns, use information, or adapt and learn.
records.description_with_prereqs: Discusses complexity analysis from various points of view to the benefit of human-centered design. Covers how large numbers of relatively simple entities organize themselves without any central controller acting collectively to create patterns, use information, or adapt and learn.

records.subject: HUM
records.description: Surveys world art history and methodology from circa 1500 to present day. (HU/SS) (LA)

records.subject: HUM
records.description: Introduces the grammar of Western music through music theory. Teaches skills in pitch and rhythm notation, and the fundamentals of melody, harmony and time. (Requirements: Listed prerequisite and one additional humanities course from the humanities core course list.) (HU/SS) (LA)

records.subject: HUM
records.description: Explores social, political, artistic and psychological aspects of the image of the monstrous as seen through the lens of fiction. (HU/SS) (LA)

(Prerequisites: CSE 1502, CSE 1503, MAE 3061, MAE 3161, MAE 3083)

records.title: Fluid Mechanics
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Introduces fluid variables; fluid statics; flow kinematics; equations of mass, momentum and energy conservation in both integral and differential formulations; similitude and dimensional analysis; the stress tensor; inviscid and viscous flows; flow in pipes; laminar and turbulent flows.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces fluid variables; fluid statics; flow kinematics; equations of mass, momentum and energy conservation in both integral and differential formulations; similitude and dimensional analysis; the stress tensor; inviscid and viscous flows; flow in pipes; laminar and turbulent flows. (Prerequisites: MAE 2082, PHY 3011, MTH 2201, MAE 2082, PHY 3011, MTH 2201, MTH 2001)

records.title: Compressible Flow
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies high-speed compressible flow. Extends boundary-layer theory to the compressible case. Also includes normal and oblique shocks; compressible flow in ducts and nozzles; Mach waves; Prandtl-Meyer expansions; method of characteristics; unsteady 1D flows; and conical flow.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies high-speed compressible flow. Extends boundary-layer theory to the compressible case. Also includes normal and oblique shocks; compressible flow in ducts and nozzles; Mach waves; Prandtl-Meyer expansions; method of characteristics; unsteady 1D flows; and conical flow. (Prerequisites: MAE 3161, MAE 3191)

records.title: Engr Thermodynamics 1
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies the conservation of energy and mass in closed- and open-flow systems. Includes the physical properties and equations of state for pure substances; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; and reversible processes and Carnot cycle.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the conservation of energy and mass in closed- and open-flow systems. Includes the physical properties and equations of state for pure substances; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; and reversible processes and Carnot cycle. (Prerequisites: CHM 1101, MTH 2001, PHY 1001)

records.title: Engr Thermodynamics 1
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies the conservation of energy and mass in closed- and open-flow systems. Includes the physical properties and equations of state for pure substances; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; and reversible processes and Carnot cycle.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the conservation of energy and mass in closed- and open-flow systems. Includes the physical properties and equations of state for pure substances; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; and reversible processes and Carnot cycle. records.title: Engr Thermodynamics 1
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies the conservation of energy and mass in closed- and open-flow systems. Includes the physical properties and equations of state for pure substances; the first and second laws of thermodynamics; and reversible processes and Carnot cycle.

records.title: Engr Thermodynamics 2
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Practical problems involving power and refrigeration cycles and chemical thermodynamics, the combustion process and compressible flows as examined in applications involving nozzles and blade passages.
records.description_with_prereqs: Practical problems involving power and refrigeration cycles and chemical thermodynamics, the combustion process and compressible flows as examined in applications involving nozzles and blade passages. (Prerequisites: MAE 3191)

records.title: Aerodynamics & Flt Mech
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Dynamics of frictionless fluid including the effects of unsteadiness and three-dimensionality; tools and rules for the construction of elementary flows about bodies, flows about airfoils and wings in three dimensions.
records.description_with_prereqs: Dynamics of frictionless fluid including the effects of unsteadiness and three-dimensionality; tools and rules for the construction of elementary flows about bodies, flows about airfoils and wings in three dimensions. (Prerequisites: MAE 3161)

records.title: AE Junior Design
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Introduces the concepts and methodology of rational aerospace design through interaction with seniors completing their capstone design projects and development of team proposals for capstone design projects that will be implemented during the senior year. (Requirement: Junior standing.) (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces the concepts and methodology of rational aerospace design through interaction with seniors completing their capstone design projects and development of team proposals for capstone design projects that will be implemented during the senior year. (Requirement: Junior standing.) (Q)

records.title: Control Systems
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Stresses both classical and modern control methodologies. Includes frequency and time-domain representation of linear systems, stability analysis and design techniques.
records.description_with_prereqs: Stresses both classical and modern control methodologies. Includes frequency and time-domain representation of linear systems, stability analysis and design techniques. (Prerequisites: MTH 2201)

records.title: Control Systems
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Stresses both classical and modern control methodologies. Includes frequency and time-domain representation of linear systems, stability analysis and design techniques.
records.description_with_prereqs: Stresses both classical and modern control methodologies. Includes frequency and time-domain representation of linear systems, stability analysis and design techniques. (Prerequisites: MTH 2201)

records.title: Thermal Systems Design
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Radiative heat transfer applications in thermal systems. Elementary methods of optimization for design. Application of thermodynamics, fluid mechanics and heat transfer. Equipment fundamentals with emphasis on heat exchanger design and analysis. Design projects involving use of software and laboratory experiments.
records.description_with_prereqs: Radiative heat transfer applications in thermal systems. Elementary methods of optimization for design. Application of thermodynamics, fluid mechanics and heat transfer. Equipment fundamentals with emphasis on heat exchanger design and analysis. Design projects involving use of software and laboratory experiments. (Prerequisites: MAE 4171)

records.title: Heat Transfer Laboratory
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques.
records.description_with_prereqs: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques. (Prerequisites: MAE 4171)

records.title: Heat Transfer Laboratory
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques.
records.description_with_prereqs: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques. (Prerequisites: MAE 4171)

records.title: Heat Transfer Laboratory
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques.
records.description_with_prereqs: Reinforces the activities associated with MAE 4071 and MAE 4171. Investigates the physics of heat transfer (conduction, convection, radiation) through the use of modern experimental techniques. (Prerequisites: MAE 4171)

records.title: Princ of Heat Transfer
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Steady state and transient heat conduction for one- and multidimensional systems; free and forced convection in both internal and external flows for both laminar and turbulent conditions; boiling and condensation. Introduces radiation properties, blackbody radiation and surface emission.
records.description_with_prereqs: Steady state and transient heat conduction for one- and multidimensional systems; free and forced convection in both internal and external flows for both laminar and turbulent conditions; boiling and condensation. Introduces radiation properties, blackbody radiation and surface emission. (Prerequisites: MAE 3161, MAE 3191, MTH 3210)

records.title: HVAC
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Air-vapor mixture properties and psychometrics, solar radiation in heating and air conditioning applications, heating/cooling load calculations, annual energy consumption, heat generation and cooling processes.
records.description_with_prereqs: Air-vapor mixture properties and psychometrics, solar radiation in heating and air conditioning applications, heating/cooling load calculations, annual energy consumption, heat generation and cooling processes. (Prerequisites: MAE 4171)

records.title: Dsgn Methodologies
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Covers engineering ethics and design methodologies with case studies. Presents relevant design projects and case studies by faculty and invited engineers representing local industry. Requires development of a proposal for MAE 4193. (Requirement: Junior standing in mechanical engineering.) (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Covers engineering ethics and design methodologies with case studies. Presents relevant design projects and case studies by faculty and invited engineers representing local industry. Requires development of a proposal for MAE 4193. (Requirement: Junior standing in mechanical engineering.) (Q) (Prerequisites: COM 2223, COM 2223)

records.title: Mech Eng Dsgn 2
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Student teams complete their design projects. Details of engineering analyses and prototype construction and testing results including sensitivity, optimization and cost analyses are presented and outlined in a written final report. Oral presentations are made to faculty and engineers from participating industry. (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Student teams complete their design projects. Details of engineering analyses and prototype construction and testing results including sensitivity, optimization and cost analyses are presented and outlined in a written final report. Oral presentations are made to faculty and engineers from participating industry. (Q) (Prerequisites: MAE 4193)

records.title: Aircraft Stab & Control
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Static stability of an airplane in pitch and sideslip; static manual control; general equations of unsteady motion; the stability of derivatives; stability of uncontrolled motion (lateral and longitudinal), including characteristic motions, their frequencies and their rates of decay.
records.description_with_prereqs: Static stability of an airplane in pitch and sideslip; static manual control; general equations of unsteady motion; the stability of derivatives; stability of uncontrolled motion (lateral and longitudinal), including characteristic motions, their frequencies and their rates of decay. (Prerequisites: MAE 3241)

records.title: Air-Breathing Engines
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies the performance analysis and component design of air-breathing engines. Includes ideal and actual cycle analyses, thrust and efficiency considerations, the flows in inlets and diffusers, combustors and nozzles, as well as compressors and turbines.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the performance analysis and component design of air-breathing engines. Includes ideal and actual cycle analyses, thrust and efficiency considerations, the flows in inlets and diffusers, combustors and nozzles, as well as compressors and turbines. (Prerequisites: MAE 3162)

records.title: Aerospace Structural Des
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Bending, shear and torsion of open and closed sections, bending of thin plates, structural instability; stress analysis of aircraft components, introduction to finite element methods, airworthiness and elementary aeroelasticity. Stresses design issues in all topics.
records.description_with_prereqs: Bending, shear and torsion of open and closed sections, bending of thin plates, structural instability; stress analysis of aircraft components, introduction to finite element methods, airworthiness and elementary aeroelasticity. Stresses design issues in all topics. (Prerequisites: MAE 3083, MTH 2201)

records.title: Aero Eng Structures Lab
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Experimental testing of structures and structural components. Presents a variety of testing methods and uses a variety of materials, including advanced composites. Introduces topics in experimental stress analysis. Emphasizes hands-on involvement by students in all areas.
records.description_with_prereqs: Experimental testing of structures and structural components. Presents a variety of testing methods and uses a variety of materials, including advanced composites. Introduces topics in experimental stress analysis. Emphasizes hands-on involvement by students in all areas. (Prerequisites: MAE 3083)

records.title: Aero Eng Structures Lab
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Experimental testing of structures and structural components. Presents a variety of testing methods and uses a variety of materials, including advanced composites. Introduces topics in experimental stress analysis. Emphasizes hands-on involvement by students in all areas.

records.description: Experimental testing of structures and structural components. Presents a variety of testing methods and uses a variety of materials, including advanced composites. Introduces topics in experimental stress analysis. Emphasizes hands-on involvement by students in all areas.

records.title: Aero Eng Design 2
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Design of an aircraft, spacecraft or component to meet desired needs. Students are given a simulated request for proposals including a measure of merit and a set of specifications that a satisfactory design must meet. Teams work under faculty supervision to develop a design to best meet these requirements. Students present their designs in written reports at the end of each semester. Lectures, readings and group discussions introduce some of the ethical and legal issues that engineers must face. (Q)
records.description_with_prereqs: Design of an aircraft, spacecraft or component to meet desired needs. Students are given a simulated request for proposals including a measure of merit and a set of specifications that a satisfactory design must meet. Teams work under faculty supervision to develop a design to best meet these requirements. Students present their designs in written reports at the end of each semester. Lectures, readings and group discussions introduce some of the ethical and legal issues that engineers must face. (Q) (Prerequisites: MAE 4291)

records.title: Space Mission Engineering
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Discusses the multidisciplinary challenges of spacecraft systems design. Provides an overview of types and applications of spacecraft. Includes economics and regulations of space flight. Discusses design and performance trade-offs. Also gives an overview of testing requirements and methods. (Requirement: Senior standing.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Discusses the multidisciplinary challenges of spacecraft systems design. Provides an overview of types and applications of spacecraft. Includes economics and regulations of space flight. Discusses design and performance trade-offs. Also gives an overview of testing requirements and methods. (Requirement: Senior standing.) (Prerequisites: MAE 2201, MTH 2201)

records.title: Applications in FEM
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Emphasizes finite element simulation methods for problems in mechanical design; static solutions; eigenvalue techniques in stability and dynamic analysis; direct and reduced basis formulation of dynamical equations; analyses of structures; use of commercially available software. (Requirement: Background knowledge of mechanics of materials.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Emphasizes finite element simulation methods for problems in mechanical design; static solutions; eigenvalue techniques in stability and dynamic analysis; direct and reduced basis formulation of dynamical equations; analyses of structures; use of commercially available software. (Requirement: Background knowledge of mechanics of materials.)

records.title: Experimental Fluid Dynamics
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Introduces students to test facilities such as wind tunnels and water tanks. Includes measurements of force and pressure distribution on airfoil principles and applications of laser Doppler velocimetry, hot-wire anemometry, flow visualization methods and modern data acquisition systems (LabView). (Requirement: Background knowledge in fluid mechanics.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces students to test facilities such as wind tunnels and water tanks. Includes measurements of force and pressure distribution on airfoil principles and applications of laser Doppler velocimetry, hot-wire anemometry, flow visualization methods and modern data acquisition systems (LabView). (Requirement: Background knowledge in fluid mechanics.)

records.title: Radiation Heat Transfer
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Development of radiative properties from electromagnetic theory; theory and analysis of shape factors; enclosure radiative transfer with diffuse-gray and nongray surfaces; and an introduction to radiative transfer within participating media and semitransparent solids. (Requirement: Background knowledge of heat transfer.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Development of radiative properties from electromagnetic theory; theory and analysis of shape factors; enclosure radiative transfer with diffuse-gray and nongray surfaces; and an introduction to radiative transfer within participating media and semitransparent solids. (Requirement: Background knowledge of heat transfer.)

records.title: Solar Energy Analysis
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies solar radiation principles, data estimation and prediction. Reviews heat transfer principles, and radiation and optical properties of surfaces. Includes flat plate solar collector analysis and analysis of concentrating collectors, solar energy storage, and solar heating/air conditioning and refrigeration systems. (Requirement: Background knowledge of heat transfer.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies solar radiation principles, data estimation and prediction. Reviews heat transfer principles, and radiation and optical properties of surfaces. Includes flat plate solar collector analysis and analysis of concentrating collectors, solar energy storage, and solar heating/air conditioning and refrigeration systems. (Requirement: Background knowledge of heat transfer.)

records.title: Sel Top Heat Trans/Energy
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Advanced topics reflecting the current research interests of the faculty and visiting scholars. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Advanced topics reflecting the current research interests of the faculty and visiting scholars. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)

records.title: Instrumentation and Meas
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Studies the fundamentals of sensors and measurements for engineering applications, and software/hardware tools for development of computer-based instrumentation systems. Includes analog signals, signal conditioning, programming virtual instruments, communication standards, data acquisition and process control.
records.description_with_prereqs: Studies the fundamentals of sensors and measurements for engineering applications, and software/hardware tools for development of computer-based instrumentation systems. Includes analog signals, signal conditioning, programming virtual instruments, communication standards, data acquisition and process control.

records.title: Internal Combust Engines
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Investigates the applications of thermodynamic, fluid dynamic and combustion principles to spark- and compression-ignition engines, and direct-injection stratified charge engines; ideal and actual cycle analyses; exhaust emissions, air pollution and control; engine heat transfer; and engine modeling.
records.description_with_prereqs: Investigates the applications of thermodynamic, fluid dynamic and combustion principles to spark- and compression-ignition engines, and direct-injection stratified charge engines; ideal and actual cycle analyses; exhaust emissions, air pollution and control; engine heat transfer; and engine modeling.

records.title: Gas Turbines
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Introduces characteristics, performance analyses and design methodologies for stationary aircraft gas turbines. Topics include gas turbine cycle analyses, component design of combustors, compressors, turbines and nozzles, fluid dynamics and heat transfer, gas turbine fuels and emissions.
records.description_with_prereqs: Introduces characteristics, performance analyses and design methodologies for stationary aircraft gas turbines. Topics include gas turbine cycle analyses, component design of combustors, compressors, turbines and nozzles, fluid dynamics and heat transfer, gas turbine fuels and emissions.

records.title: Elasticity
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Analyzes stress and strain in two and three dimensions, equilibrium, compatibility and constitutive equations, energy methods, flexure, stretching, torsion and contact stress formulations, axially symmetric problems. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Analyzes stress and strain in two and three dimensions, equilibrium, compatibility and constitutive equations, energy methods, flexure, stretching, torsion and contact stress formulations, axially symmetric problems. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)

records.title: Advanced Dynamics
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Newtonian and analytical mechanics; rigid-body dynamics, Euler's equations and spinning bodies; Lagrange's equations, Routhian and Hamiltonian mechanics, canonical transformations and Hamilton-Jacobi theory; dissipative, gyroscopic and circulatory systems; applications of numerical methods to complex dynamics problems.
records.description_with_prereqs: Newtonian and analytical mechanics; rigid-body dynamics, Euler's equations and spinning bodies; Lagrange's equations, Routhian and Hamiltonian mechanics, canonical transformations and Hamilton-Jacobi theory; dissipative, gyroscopic and circulatory systems; applications of numerical methods to complex dynamics problems.

records.title: Sel Top Systems/Dynamics
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Addresses selected topics reflecting the current research interests of the faculty and visiting scholars. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Addresses selected topics reflecting the current research interests of the faculty and visiting scholars. (Requirement: Instructor approval.)

records.title: Stability FTE
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Examines techniques to evaluate airplane stability and control by flight testing. Includes flight labs for flight test data collection. Presents methods for stick fixed and stick free extrapolation of stability neutral points and control characteristics. Also includes effects of high speed and transonic flight due to aircraft configuration. (Requirement: Program chair approval.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Examines techniques to evaluate airplane stability and control by flight testing. Includes flight labs for flight test data collection. Presents methods for stick fixed and stick free extrapolation of stability neutral points and control characteristics. Also includes effects of high speed and transonic flight due to aircraft configuration. (Requirement: Program chair approval.)

records.title: Helicopter Flight Test
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Examines flight test engineering techniques to determine helicopter performance. Includes flight labs for data collection. Presents theory and methods for measuring hover, climb and level-flight performance. Addresses differences between airplane and helicopter flight testing.
records.description_with_prereqs: Examines flight test engineering techniques to determine helicopter performance. Includes flight labs for data collection. Presents theory and methods for measuring hover, climb and level-flight performance. Addresses differences between airplane and helicopter flight testing.

records.title: Nonlinear Cont Sys
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Includes nonlinear system fundamentals (stability and dynamic peculiarities, methods of nonlinear analysis); basic nonlinear control methods (sliding control and feedback linearization, multidimensional extension); advanced nonlinear control methods (adaptive control, neural networks); and nonlinear control applications. (Requirement: Background knowledge of control systems.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes nonlinear system fundamentals (stability and dynamic peculiarities, methods of nonlinear analysis); basic nonlinear control methods (sliding control and feedback linearization, multidimensional extension); advanced nonlinear control methods (adaptive control, neural networks); and nonlinear control applications. (Requirement: Background knowledge of control systems.)

records.title: Guid/Nav Aero Vehicles
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Includes the principles for guidance and navigation of spacecraft, launch vehicles and missiles. Applies nonlinear programming, calculus of variations and optimal control to flight and trajectory optimization. Covers ballistic and adaptive pursuit guidance; orbit determination and celestial navigation; recursive navigation; GPS and Kalman filtering.
records.description_with_prereqs: Includes the principles for guidance and navigation of spacecraft, launch vehicles and missiles. Applies nonlinear programming, calculus of variations and optimal control to flight and trajectory optimization. Covers ballistic and adaptive pursuit guidance; orbit determination and celestial navigation; recursive navigation; GPS and Kalman filtering. (Prerequisites: MAE 5802)

records.title: Final Semester Thesis
records.subject: MAE
records.description: Variable registration for thesis completion after satisfaction of minimum registration requirements. (Requirements: Accepted petition to graduate and approval by Office of Graduate Programs.)
records.description_with_prereqs: Variable registration for thesis completion after satisfaction of minimum registration requirements. (Requirements: Accepted petition to graduate and approval by Office of Graduate Programs.)
